<TEXT>
the us supreme court on thursday denied a 
lastminute appeal by a man scheduled to die friday in floridas 
electric chair for killing two police officers 14 years ago 
the high court in an order released at 1112 pm edt denied a 
stay of execution for jesse tafero justices william brennan and 
thurgood marshall who are opposed to any use of the death penalty 
dissented 
earlier in the day the 11th us circuit court of appeals in 
atlanta turned tafero down only hours after us district judge 
lenore nesbitt in miami refused to issue a writ of habeas corpus in 
the case 
the stay issued by judge nesbitt remained in effect until 7 am 
the supreme court had also rejected an appeal by tafero earlier 
this week 
mark olive appeals attorney for tafero refused to comment on 
the court decisions 
tafero 43 now on death row at florida state prison near 
starke is scheduled to die at 701 am friday for the 1976 
slaying of a florida highway patrol trooper and a canadian 
constable 
he would be the 22nd person executed in florida and the 124th 
nationally since the 1976 us supreme court ruling allowing states 
to resume use of the death penalty 
the states last execution occurred exactly one year ago friday 
when former prison guard aubrey d adams was executed for killing a 
young girl 
tafero his girlfriend sonja jacobs her two children and 
traveling companion walter rhodes jr were sleeping in a a car 
parked in a rest area on interstate 95 near pompano beach on feb 
20 1976 when the two victims approached 
trooper phillip black and visiting canadian constable donald 
irwin of kitchener ontario were killed when they checked on the 
car black died from gunshot wounds to the head and neck while 
irwin received fatal wounds to his right eye and shoulder 
in court there was a dispute over who did the shooting 
rhodes who received three concurrent life terms testified that 
tafero and ms jacobs killed the officers both were convicted and 
sentenced to death but ms jacobs sentence was commuted to life 
in prison in 1981 
tafero a native of jersey city nj has a long juvenile 
record and served six years in prison before the killings 
his codefendants remain in florida prisons 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

