<TEXT>
heavily armed police 
poured into this mohawk reservation after two people were slain 
but gov mario cuomo on wednesday ruled out force to put down a 
9monthold dispute over gambling 
us and canadian police sealed off the 28000acre reservation 
that straddles the border 
cuomo said he had ordered the new york army national guard to 
assist state police but would not order guardsmen onto the 
reservation 
we will not send military force because of the risk of 
bloodshed because of what it would provoke cuomo told reporter 
in albany 
before you use military force you should use the force of 
reason 
representatives from six governments were tentatively scheduled 
to meet thursday in montreal to discuss the st regis sovereignty 
issue according to micha menczer attorney for the mohawk council 
officials from ontario quebec and new york federal officials 
from the us and canada and indian leaders will be represented at 
the talks which will include discussion of the removal of weapons 
from the reservation and the restoration of law and order menczer 
said 
new york state police carrying shotguns and the quebec 
provincial force entered the reservation tuesday night and 
wednesday after weeks of violence between pro and antigambling 
factions culminated in the shooting deaths of two mohawk men 
earlier in the day 
cuomo said the national guard was used to transport troopers and 
provide equipment at armories in nearby towns 
on the canadian side canadian troops provided communications 
assistance 
state troopers denied entry onto the reservation to everyone but 
residents they would not divulge the number of troopers on the 
reservation but residents said the combined uscanadian police 
forces numbered in the hundreds 
weve got an armed invasion said diane lazores a 
spokeswoman for the warrior society an armed progambling group 
lazores said state police also were restricting movement of 
residents within the reservation despite promises made before the 
action 
if they want an international incident theyre going to get 
one she said 
the reservation was peaceful wednesday after nearly a month of 
nights filled with sporadic gunfire and brawls 
young mohawk children waited for their school bus beside armed 
state troopers while many other mohawks of all ages stayed at home 
im not venturing out said reservation resident jack 
hubert a recent retiree i dont want to spend my golden years 
being shot at 
hubert like the large majority of the approximately 9000 
people living on the reservation has taken no direct part in the 
feuding between the two mohawk factions 
were not all looking to get shot just a few are he said 
up to 600 mohawks fled to a refugee center in ontario last week 
after a week of nightly violence 
junior edwards whose body was found near his home in snye 
quebec on tuesday was described by members of the warrior society 
as progambling matthew pyke was shot to death early tuesday while 
walking to the house of a fellow antigambling activist 
officials said the deaths prompted state police to break their 
policy of not setting foot on the reservation unless invited by 
mohawk leaders 
state police capt richard garrant said troopers would stay on 
mohawk land to maintain some type of stability until further 
orders arrived from the governors office 
fletcher graves a mediator from the us justice department who 
has helped the mohawks resolve other disputes arrived on the 
reservation wednesday afternoon according to warriors society 
member john boots 
earlier graves said i dont know what my role will be until 
i get there well talk to every party 
in washington white house press secretary marlin fitzwater said 
the bush administration would not get involved we have no 
intention to intervene he said its a matter that needs to be 
resolved locally 
boots said state police maj robert leu also arrived to speak 
with the mohawks 
he said the presence of the state police beyond investigating 
the two deaths was a doublecross and the warriors have asked 
the state police to dismantle their roadblocks and leave the 
reservation 
i dont want to make a comment on what the reprisal would be 
when 10000 indians get angry boots said 
barbara barnes spokeswoman for the antigambling faction said 
she was glad that police would be on the reservation 
people here have no peace of mind as soon as the police 
leave the shots will start again she said 
the issue of gambling on the reservation has been at the center 
of escalating violence since last summer when an fbiled gambling 
raid triggered a 12day standoff between a progambling group and 
state police 
the fbi claimed the mohawks had violated federal gaming 
regulations the mohawks claim they are not bound by state or 
federal gambling laws 
progambling forces say the reservations six casinos whose 
slot machines craps tables and other games draw busloads of 
patrons are an economic boon opponents argue they encourage 
prostitution and drug use and threaten traditional ways 
last summer a mob of antigamblers burned down a casino 
sporadic violence were reported in the fall and winter but 
tensions mounted in march when gambling opponents blockaded roads 
to keep outsiders away from the highstakes casinos 
last week progamblers tore down the blockades in a hail of 
gunfire 
</TEXT>
