president vaclav havel says secret 
police files will be made available to political parties so they 
may avoid scandal by screening their candidates prior to elections 
at the request of the political party involved such screening 
could be done consensus among political parties has been reached 
in that respect havel told a news conference on wednesday the 
party would then consider the candidates fitness to run for office 
nobody wants a situation such as we have seen in east germany 
where such things secret police affiliation were used during and 
even after the elections as an instrument of political struggle 
havel said 
these things can be done in a more decent way he added 
indicating that some potential candidates may indeed have 
cooperated with the secret police of the communist regime toppled 
in last falls peaceful revolution 
two prominent east german leaders including former social 
democrat chief ibrahim boehme resigned this year amid allegations 
they had ties to the secret police of the ousted communists 
czechoslovakias first free elections in more than four decades 
are scheduled for june 8 
