hospital receiving treatment for a blood clot in his left leg 
dr stuart grossman a neurosurgeon and oncologist at johns 
hopkins university school of medicine in baltimore said blood 
clots are not unusual for brain tumor patients 
something predisposes patients with brain tumors to develop 
clots in the legs he said we dont know why that is 
patients with clots are treated with a blood thinner and 
generally do quite well he said 
matalin said she and pollster robert teeter visited atwater at 
the hospital sunday and reviewed data on 1990 races 
this was the best hes been she said according to matalin 
