<TEXT>
a threecar amtrak train en route from 
chicago to indianapolis derailed wednesday night injuring more 
than 20 people authorities said 
the accident occurred shortly before 9 pm edt on the eastern 
edge of crawfordsville about 60 miles northwest of indianapolis 
state police said 
amtrak spokeswoman pat kelly said 27 people were being taken to 
a local hospital 
david callecod spokesman for culver union hospital in 
crawfordsville said 24 people had arrived by early thursday 
morning 
he said one person was admitted with a concussion and another 
would be admitted for undetermined injuries while the others were 
being treated for minor injuries such as bumps and bruises 
callecod said earlier that as many as 30 people were to be taken 
to the hospital 
indiana state police trooper mark cornell who was at the scene 
said the train was switching tracks when it apparently struck the 
rear end of a stationary freight car and derailed 
it didnt look like there was an incredible amount of 
damage he said 
kelley said approximately 35 passengers and crew were aboard the 
regularily scheduled run from chicago to indianapolis 
about 25 crawfordsville firefighters were on the scene but 
there were no reports of any fires said fire department spokesman 
bill myers 
the derailment was the second for amtrak in as many weeks on 
april 22 at least 91 people were reported hurt three seriously 
when the national passenger rail lines california zephyr derailed 
in iowa en route to chicago 
