<TEXT>
after losing a 30month battle 
against extradition joseph schwammberger was flown to west germany 
to face charges he oversaw or took part in the slaughter of 
thousands of jews as head of a nazi labor camp 
schwammberger 78 was put aboard a lufthansa commercial flight 
to frankfurt on wednesday accompanied by a doctor his attorney and 
west german officials of interpol the international police 
organization 
argentinas supreme court late last month upheld the extradition 
of schwammberger who fled to argentina after escaping from allied 
authorities in the late 1940s but was captured at an argentine 
ranch in 1987 
he is charged with provoking the deaths of several thousand 
jews and of personally killing some said wolfgang siegel a 
spokesman for the west german embassy 
siegel said that after arriving in frankfurt schwammberger 
would be taken to stuttgart site of the court that had asked for 
his extradition 
schwammberger is accused of commanding forced labor camps at 
przemysl and mielec in nazioccupied poland at which thousands of 
inmates mostly jews were executed survivors testified he starved 
prisoners used dogs to tear them apart and threw people alive 
into fires 
rabbi marvin hier of the simon wiesenthal center in los angeles 
which gathered evidence against schwammberger said in a telephone 
interview here we are not dealing with an administrator but 
with a man who participated directly a man who rolled up his 
sleeves and bloodied his hands every day 
this case will be exceptional in the sense that 45 years after 
the crimes were committed the accused will be brought to trial 
hier said adding that the center has 73 witnesses who are prepared 
to testify against schwammberger 
hier said schwammberger was arrested by the french army in 1945 
but escaped three years later from a train taking him to us 
military authorities in austria for trial 
using his own name schwammberger eventually settled in 
argentina worked at a petrochemical plant in la plata 30 miles 
south of the buenos aires and obtained argentine citizenship in 
1965 hier reported 
a stuttgart court ordered his arrest in 1973 at the time he 
was believed to be living in argentina where there is a sizeable 
population of germanspeaking immigrants many nazis fled to south 
america following the defeat of adolf hitlers germany 
in october 1987 the simon wiesenthal center placed 
schwammberger on its most wanted nazi war criminals list argentine 
newspapers published the list and police received information 
about schwammberger 
he was taken into custody on nov 13 1987 at a ranch in huerta 
grande 500 miles northwest of buenos aires he has been held in 
jail since 
defense attorneys asked argentina to reject an extradition 
request on the ground that schwammberger was an argentine citizen 
or to hold the trial in argentina 
the federal appeals court in la plata rejected their argument in 
august ruling that the crimes schwammberger is accused of 
committing occurred before he was an argentine citizen the supreme 
court upheld that ruling on march 23 
in 1960 adolph eichmann a major figure in devising the final 
solution in which jews were rounded up and executed was 
kidnapped in buenos aires by israeli agents convicted at a trial 
in jerusalem and hanged 
dutch officials have asked argentine police to look for abraham 
kipp who was sentenced to death for crimes committed against jews 
during the war in 1953 kipp was naturalized as an argentine 
citizen 
