president bush said today that he has invited 
congressional leaders to the white house on sunday to begin the 
search for a compromise on the 1991 federal budget 
what we have to do is start talking process and how we go 
forward the president said at a white house news conference 
im not going to sit here and do nothing 
after a slow start the house approved a 12 trillion budget 
tuesday for next year and the senate budget committee approved one 
of its own on wednesday both spending plans were written by 
democrats and impose cuts of about 10 billion in the defense 
programs bush wants 
the president said he decided to ask for the meeting because of 
the recent budget movement in congress 
now there seems to be more action so it seemed to me to be a 
good time to sit down and talk process and see where we go now 
he said 
bush denied that the meeting would be a bargaining session 
saying were not into a negotiation were talking process 
