it would take 3069 billion to allow military programs to stay 
even with inflation this years spending is estimated at 2963 
billion 
the house approved its own democraticwritten budget on tuesday 
that cuts defense spending to 2955 billion 
besides saving 13 billion from defense the senate panels plan 
would chop 36 billion from domestic and foreign aid programs 
bush proposed only a 400 million cut 
