modernize nucleartipped artillary will be particularily popular in 
west germany where most are deployed 
bush said hed issued the call for a summit of leaders from the 
16 members of the north atlantic treaty alliance after consulting 
personally with my nato colleagues the session would launch a 
wideranging strategy review for the transformed europe of the 
1990s 
bush said the intelligence community was trying to determine now 
whether the releases of former hostages robert polhill and frank 
reed were part of a process that would lead to freedom for the 
remaining six americans in captivity 
bush said he was prepared to do anything that wouldnt be 
perceived as negotiating for the release of hostages he said he 
was willing to try to determine the fate of four iranians kidnapped 
in beirut in 1982 but said they were believed dead 
ive tried hard not to raise the hopes of the hostage 
families and then have them dashed he said 
bush reiterated the us position that the united states wanted 
to see all hostages released but sidestepped commenting on 
whether this should also include 400 shiites being held by israel 
iran has demanded that these prisoners be released including 
moslem leader sheik obeid 
i want to see all hostages released in all countries 
bush said but he said there were definitional problems 
concerning those held by israel because some people view people 
they hold as having broken laws and some people dont 
bush was to meet later in the day with lithuanian prime minister 
kazimiera prunskiene he embraced the statement from lithuanian 
president landsbergis that seemed to lessen chances of a 
confrontation between lithuanian leaders and moscow 
whatever facilitates dialogue is good bush said at the 
same time bush indicated there was no change in us position 
toward moscow over the crisis in lithuania 
he denied that his administrations proposal the day before for 
relaxing export controls on western hightech products sent to the 
soviet union and eastern europe had been any form of reward for 
moscows restraint 
bush made the nato announcements as secretary of state james a 
baker iii met in brussels with nato allies 
baker proposed that 35 foreign ministers from east and west meet 
in new york in late september to pave the way for a summit by the 
end of the year to formally sign agreements to reduce conventional 
forces throughout europe 
on other subjects 
bush said that i didnt tell you im anxious to see bill 
seidman leave as head of the fdic but neither did he urge 
