israel and bulgaria restored diplomatic 
relations today after a 23year break and signed an economic 
cooperation agreement 
bulgaria and other east bloc countries broke relations with 
israel after the 1967 sixday war and only moscow has not restored 
diplomatic ties following the democratic reforms that have swept 
eastern europe 
foreign ministers moshe arens of israel and boiko dimitrov of 
bulgaria signed a formal agreement to resume relations then held a 
news conference at the palace of culture 
about 100 palestinian students demonstrated outside to protest 
israels policy in the middle east 
the plo mission issued a statement acknowledging bulgarias 
right to restore relations with israel and expressed hope that 
friendly relations between palestinians and bulgaria would continue 
repeating comments made upon his arrival wednesday arens said 
bulgaria is almost a neighbor of israel and many jews of 
bulgarian origin are an integral part of israeli society he said 
arens said israels image is better now because some socialist 
countries recognize the jewish state and no longer give 
unconditional support to arab nations 
dimitrov and arens also signed a protocol on economic 
cooperation that covers air transportation telecommunications 
tourism agriculture mutual protection of investments and dealings 
between the countries national banks 
