new york ap retail sales generally rebounded in april as 
consumers returned to stores to shop for easter and spring items 
several of the nations biggest retailers reported today 
many retailers who had a dismal march posted better results last 
month woolworth corp whose sales fell in march compared to a 
year earlier had an 182 percent sales gain in april at stores 
open at least a year and a 211 percent increase overall 
results from stores open a year or longer known as same or 
comparablestore sales give a more accurate reading of a 
retailers performance industry analysts therefore give them more 
weight than overall sales figures 
changes in the calendar such as easter falling on april 9 this 
year and on march 26 last year often have an impact on retail 
sales and affect yeartoyear comparisons but after accounting for 
the shift the industrys overall results were generally favorable 
said jeffrey feiner a retail analyst with merrill lynch amp co 
analysts consider march and april sales together in assessing 
how well a store has performed 
shoppers again spent most of their money on apparel and 
lowerpriced items while generally shying away from more expensive 
purchases consumers remained burdened by high installment debt and 
were again cautious about major expenditures 
analysts expect this trend which has been in place for several 
years to continue 
retail sales are closely watched not only as a gauge of the 
industrys health but also as an economic barometer consumer 
spending accounts for about twothirds of the gross national 
product 
sears roebuck and co the nations largest retailer reported 
a 31 percent increase over april 1989 results in samestore sales 
and a 16 percent sales gain overall 
walmart stores inc again outdistanced other retailers 
reporting a 7 percent increase in samestore sales while overall 
results were up 20 percent 
jc penney co inc had a disappointing month after a much 
stronger march penneys samestore sales fell 28 percent while 
overall sales were off 17 percent 
melville corp which runs specialty chains including thom mcan 
kaybee and cvs said its overall sales rose 219 percent melville 
did not release samestore figures 
other major retailers including dayton hudson corp and may 
department stores co are expected to announce their sales figures 
next thursday analysts said it appeared these companies which 
own some of the countrys biggest department store chains would 
report favorable results 
the results announced today differ from the federal governments 
monthly retail sales report besides stores the governments 
figures include sales at a range of establishments from auto 
dealerships and supermarkets to restaurants and movie theaters 
