beginning sunday 
us callers must add a 7 or an 8 to the string of 
numbers it takes to complete such transatlantic calls 
that means a call or fax to the american embassy in london will 
require dialing 011 the international code 44 united kingdom 
country code 71 or 81 the new london area codes plus the 
sevendigit number 
a call to the embassy would look like this 01144714999000 
previously us callers dialed 0114414999000 
british telecom says the 71 area code will be assigned to inner 
london including trafalgar square and the financial district 
while the 81 area code will be used for numbers in outer london 
such as heathrow and wimbley 
if youre in london youll have to dial either 071 or 081 if 
you call from one area code to another 
