spurred by the historic changes 
sweeping europe the united states and its 15 western allies agreed 
thursday to hold nato and eastwest summits this year to reach a 
treaty reducing troops and nonnuclear arms 
the decision was announced after secretary of state james a 
baker iii briefed nato foreign ministers on a new us nuclear 
