negotiations to reduce troops tanks artillery and other 
nonnuclear forces 
baker stressed that holding the 35nation summit depends on 
completing the conventional forces in europe cfe treaty 
unless we conclude a cfe agreement we should postpone a csce 
summit he told reporters 
the csce or conference on security and cooperation in europe 
is comprised of all the nations of europe except albania along 
with the united states and canada 
baker said the negotiations to limit soviet troops in europe to 
195000 and us forces to 225000 have not proceeded as rapidly 
as we would have thought 
