less radical than lithuanias declaration of independence march 11 
in lithuania 80 percent of the 38 million people are ethnic 
lithuanian but about 54 percent of latvias population of 27 
million people are latvian most of the rest are ethnic russians 
many of whom oppose independence 
in the past year latvia has followed lithuanias lead in 
december it abolished the communist partys guaranteed monopoly on 
power in february it condemned the 1940 act that formalized its 
annexation by the soviet union and last month a large segment of 
its communist party broke from its moscowbased parent the steps 
followed similar lithuanian actions 
the latvians are taking a slower approach to independence 
however one proposal calls for an undefined transition of several 
years before full independence estonia also set an undefined 
transition period in a declaration march 30 
the latvian proposal adopts four articles from the republics 
1922 constitution establishing an independent and democratic 
republic the historic territory of latvia giving power to the 
people and establishing a sovereign latvian parliament 
it also recognizes the legitimacy of soviet laws that do not 
contradict the republics own law 
gorbunov said the proposal took into account talks that already 
have begun with moscow 
