international law an apparent reference to the kidnap of a 
mexican doctor linked to a drug murder 
us ambassador jonathan moore representative to the un 
economic and social council did not specifically mention the 
incident involving dr alberto alvarez machain which has strained 
usmexican relations 
moore told delegates the united states believes pursuit of the 
drug menace cannot be used as a justification for violating the 
fundamental precepts of national and international law 
alvarez machain was captured in mexico by mexican bounty hunters 
on april 2 and turned over to the drug enforcement administration 
in the united states he was linked to the torturemurder of dea 
agent enrique camarena in mexico in 1985 
the united states has admitted no complicity in the crossborder 
kidnapping 
on wednesday mexicos ambassador jorge montano referred 
indirectly to the doctors abduction 
montano called for antinarcotics efforts to respect national 
sovereignty and territorial integrity and internal legislation 
he emphasized it is contradictory that certain countries 
which have a high level of drug consumption and growing internal 
production instead of joining the collective fight instead are 
acting outside the most elementary norms of international rights 
montano said mexico contends that a us supreme court decision 
of feb 28 which supported us agents abroad is an 
authorization to commit actions violating sovereignty of other 
countries 
he said mexican authorities will keep cooperating in fighting 
drug trafficking but will not allow anybody drug dealers or 
those prosecuting them to violate the rights and laws of mexico 
on thursday moore said a recent international session against 
drug trafficking recognized that no country can deal with this 
scourge alone or isolate itself from its effects 
the economic and social council is following up the general 
assembly in february and a meeting in london on issues arising from 
the illegal drug trade 
moore urged all nations to ratify the un convention against 
traffic in illicit drugs and psychotropic substances he said un 
drug control agencies have major and growing roles in international 
narcotics control 
