administration act to the full house with an amendment that would 
ban the lucrative export of rawlogs from all state lands in oregon 
and threefourths of such lands in washington 
the export controls are necessary to keep domestic mills 
operating while setting aside millions of acres to protect 
oldgrowth forests needed to save the rare northern spotted owl 
from extinction said rep john miller rwash 
