<TEXT>
the local democratic party thursday narrowly 
rejected a resolution drafted by the party chairman that would have 
requested mayor marion barry to abandon any plans to run for 
reelection in november 
the proposal was voted down by a 2923 margin after almost two 
hours of tumultous debate in which barry supporters repeatedly 
shouted insults at committee chairman josyln williams who drafted 
the resolution and others who supported it 
following the vote the mayors supporters left the district 
building hearing room shouting four more years 
barry faces trial next month on five misdemeanor cocaine 
possession charges and three felony counts of lying to a federal 
grand jury about his drug use 
the unprecedented resolution declared barrys leadership in 
question and concluded with the request that he announce that 
he will not seek renomination in 1990 
barry has not publicly disclosed his future political plans 
however he has made numerous campaignstyle appearance since his 
return to the city from seven weeks of treatment for substance 
abuse and sources close to the mayor said barry intends to run for 
a fourth fouryear term despite his impending trial 
in a letter to williams barry called the resolution 
undemocratic because it undermines the right of the voter to 
decide 
barry also said the partys action would have little influence 
on my decision about my political future 
barry did not attend the meeting but his sentiments were echoed 
by many who did 
