jay b stephens barry declined to answer the grand jurys question 
whether he had used within the past five years any illegal drug 
or substance including cocaine 
in the papers filed thursday stephens said barry consciously 
engaged in a course of conduct to corroborate the known lies of 
others that exonerated him and to remain silent about other 
matters 
barry is now accused of lying on three occasions to the panel 
once each about whether he and lewis gave each other cocaine and 
also when asked whether he was aware of lewis drug involvement 
the letter was released as stephens sought to block efforts by 
barrys attorney to have the perjury charges against the mayor 
dismissed 
a conviction on any of the perjury charges would bar him from 
holding office or seeking reelection 
neither barry nor his spokeswoman lurma rackley were 
immediately available to comment on the documents 
