<TEXT>
luciano pavarotti took the stage at the bolshoi 
theater on thursday before an elite crowd including president 
mikhail s gorbachev who attended a concert to raise money for 
victims of the armenian earthquake 
pavarotti grinning broadly and extending his arms to the 
audience sang four encores to increasingly loud cries of 
bravo and insistent applause 
the italian star dedicated one of the encores to raisa 
gorbachev seated in a box just left of the stage he met briefly 
with the president and his wife backstage after the soldout 
performance 
the gorbachevs joined in warmly applauding pavarotti on his 
first trip to the soviet union in 15 years it was the tenors 
first performance at the famed bolshoi 
theater workers said people hoping to buy the few available 
tickets began lining up at 2 am 10 hours before the box office 
opened the theater was surrounded by police 
asked why he was trying to buy a spare ticket across the street 
from the 2500seat theater engineer sasha zlorovsky said 
pavarotti is singing that says it all 
irina sukhotsky an economist couldnt get through the police 
cordon to find an acquaintance she said would have a ticket for 
her olya pivovarova a student managed to slip through but had 
little luck getting a ticket the problem was not the price but 
the availability 
pavarotti thrilled the crowd inside the redandgold trimmed 
theater with a selection of songs from bellini rossini verdi and 
others he was accompanied at the piano by leone magiera 
among the toughest critics in the hall was usher yekaterina 
vitova an opera lover who has seen stars come and go during her 30 
years at moscows most famous theater 
he has a brilliant voice she said she praised not only the 
power of his voice but his control of it and compared him to 
soviet tenor sergei lemeshev a bolshoi star in the 1950s and 1960s 
in my mind hes better than anyone we have here she said 
she also was a little concerned about pavarottis girth hes 
hefty isnt he she asked i guess they have to be in order to 
sing like that 
among those who attended the concert were such soviet luminaries 
as poet yevgeny yevtushenko magazine editor vitaly korotich 
lawyer and newspaper editor fyodor burlatsky and gorbachev adviser 
georgy shakhnazarov 
the concert was the first in a series of benefits to raise money 
to build a 30 million hospital in spitak in armenia the city was 
destroyed by an earthquake in december 1988 that killed 25000 
people in northern armenia 
pavarotti has performed twice before in the soviet union in 
1965 and in 1974 when he sang at tchaikovsky hall 
he will give three more performances in the soviet union two in 
moscow and one in leningrad he will be accompanied by the arturo 
toscanini symphony orchestra 
