are simply untrue and disingenuous 
according to an affidavit on or about january 1990 lead 
noriega attorney frank rubino discussed his retainer with another 
assistant us attorney cynthia hawkins during the course of a 
plea bargain conference on an unrelated case 
as it was being typed up mr rubino mentioned that the 
retainer he had been paid to represent gen noriega was in seven 
figures or at least 1 million according to ms hawkins 
signed statement 
rubino then asked whether i was going to go into private 
practice to make more money the affidavit said 
rubino said thursday he recalled the incident which he said 
occurred well after the united states began its invasion of panama 
on dec 20 but before noriega arrived in the united states in early 
january 
i was in her office we were all laughing and talking and 
joking he said in a telephone interview from her lips to 
gods ears it should be true he said jokingly its just 
silly 
cocounsel jon may said the government had taken seriously a 
statement that was made in jest there is no money he added 
that the defense would give more details at fridays hearing 
may also said the defense would demand that the government show 
probable cause for contending the frozen funds were drugrelated 
should prosecutors fail to do that the defense would demand the 
money be turned over to noriega he said 
the governments response stated it has frozen 20 million in 
various bank accounts but only one is in noriegas name and 
investigators do not know if that account contains any money 
stripped of its misleading and unsupported allegations 
counsels argument represents an attempt to require the government 
to pay defense counsel a higher fee said the us attorneys 
response which was also signed by prosecutors myles malman and guy 
lewis 
the defense motion filed monday said the attorneys had run out 
of money and could not hire attorneys secretaries and 
investigators to handle the complex case they said they had 
received no fees for 10 months and only a few thousand dollars in 
expense money 
noriega was indicted here in february 1988 on charges of taking 
money from colombias medellin drug cartel to make panama into a 
safe haven for cocaine smuggling noriega surrendered to us 
authorities on jan 4 two weeks after us troops invaded panama 
and is being held at the metropolitan correctional center outside 
miami 
