rcn quoted police as saying 
police said they did not know who set off the explosion and 
there was no immediate claim of responsibility 
a series of attacks on the pharmacy chain had ended when after 
gilberto rodriguez orejuela the reputed leader of the cali cartel 
sold his interest in the chain 
it was the second bombing in the city of 15 million in the last 
24 hours on wednesday two bombs were thrown at a police station 
injuring four policemen and severely damaging the building 
traffickers have been blamed for the deaths of nearly 300 people 
in terrorist attacks since august 1989 when the government 
declared war on traffickers 
