a simple combination of bright light at night and total darkness 
during the day can help nightshift workers quickly adapt to their 
upsidedown hours researchers found 
the approach appears to be the first quick practical cure for 
the nightshift blues the onthejob sleepiness and daytime 
insomnia that plague many of the nations 7 million night workers 
