<TEXT>
something about nebraska sen bob kerrey sends 
normally cynical democrats into a swoon 
hes a softspoken sensitivelooking war hero who quotes yeats 
and dates actress debra winger raises money by the bushel and has 
a 75 percentplus approval rating in a conservative republican 
state 
hes an ambitious man yet by all accounts a man who could 
easily walk away from politics friends and acquaintances speak 
admiringly of his daring his independence his humility his 
curiosity his depth his kindness 
they compare him to john kennedy and gary hart jerry brown and 
david letterman mario cuomo after the 1984 democratic convention 
they talk about his star quality his medal of honor his blue eyes 
he might as well have hot presidential prospect stamped on 
his high pale forehead 
the guy has made an impression like nobody ive seen in a long 
time said dan payne a democratic media consultant based in 
boston 
everything about him is unusual by any standard said 
harrison hickman who has done polling for kerrey since 1982 if 
he decided to run i think he would be great ive said since i 
first met him he could be anything he wants to be 
joseph robert kerrey 46 has made his mark in many spheres he 
joined the navy as a seal lost his lower right leg in vietnam and 
came home an opponent of the war he got married had two children 
and got divorced made millions as a restauranteur served a term 
as governor and then declined to run for reelection 
but two years later in 1988 he ran for a senate seat and won 
frustrating nebraska republicans who had thought they would no 
longer be up against his charisma and apparent invincibility 
hes not only been a teflon governor but he was a teflon type of 
candidate for the us senate said state gop chairman norm 
riffel 
kerrey was sworn in only 16 months ago but already many 
democrats see in him the inspirational candidate they need to win a 
national election 
frequent media mentions and network television appearances are 
signs of what some commentators dismiss as a shortlived kerrey 
boomlet but others believe the attention will translate into 
something more significant and lasting 
hes on a roll and also on a cusp as payne puts it he can 
either go the way of jerry brown and burn out like a comet or tap 
the energy and the excitement and the brightness that emanate 
from a new star 
thus far kerreys moves in the direction of national politics 
are tentative he hasnt set up a fundraising operation bt he has 
hired bill shore a hart veteran as a top aide and traveled to 10 
states to give speeches and meet with local officials and political 
activists 
kerrey says he wants to be a good senator from nebraska but he 
hinted at a broader kerrey vision and leadership style at a 
texas democratic party dinner last february in houston 
it is important he said for us simply to reach down 
inside of ourselves and decide what we think ought to be done and 
then declare it without fear of what somebody else might say 
his priorities include universal health care investment in us 
roads water systems and other infrastructure reducing the 
national debt and establishing an educational trust corporation to 
help schools that are struggling to improve 
his primary role so far however has been as a combative and 
knowledgeable protector of the agriculture interests so vital to 
his state 
he also is closely identified with indochina he recently 
returned there on a factfinding mission his first visit to the 
region since a grenade shattered his leg and ended his military 
service 
it was hard kerrey said hesitantly when asked about the 
trip in one television interview theres an attachment there and 
at the same time theres part of me that never wants to go back 
the way i live anyway is to put that stuff behind me 
the war experience did leave a legacy of extreme caution about 
sending us troops into combat for example kerrey opposed the 
invasion of panama and he has said he does not want his son to 
confront the same decisions he did when he was a young man 
kerreys background gives him great authority and what some have 
called a bulletproof vest on issues of war peace and patriotism 
and he is outspoken on all three the political outcry over 
flagburning was a recent example 
kerrey skewered president bush for leading the charge for a 
constitutional amendment to protect the flag the president chose 
the path of least resistance and greatest political gain he said 
kerrey himself initially jumped on the same bandwagon but 
changed his view after reading supreme court opinions on the 
subject referring along the way to philosopher john stuart mill 
and the smell of my own burning flesh on a vietnam battlefield 
kerrey concluded that america does not need our government to 
protect us from those who burn a flag 
it was a characteristic reversal 
one of his hallmarks is that he always reserves the right to 
change his mind said sen james exon dneb he is one of the 
few men that ive ever heard say that as often as he does i dont 
think that means hes not dedicated to his beliefs but he always 
keeps an open mind 
which is one reason 1990 is probably too early to predict what 
kerrey will do in 1992 another is kerreys disregard for schedules 
and rulebooks and sticking to an advance plan 
one of the things that made him a marvelous combat officer was 
his ability to sense changes in field conditions and adapt to 
them said richard d herman a longtime friend who is editorial 
page editor of the lincoln journal 
kerrey can be incredibly blunt but he also has been accused of 
vagueness of new agespeak of rhetoric that loses its bearings 
nebraska republicans contend he isnt straight with constituents on 
where he stands 
people think hes telling them what they want to hear 
riffel said he can say a lot it sounds like a lot of substance 
but when you dissect it you look at it and you say what did he 
say 
riffel speculates wistfully that kerreys senate record will 
unmask him as a liberal and prove his undoing in nebraska but most 
observers believe nebraskans already know kerrey and his views 
they may not always agree with him but his appeal seems to 
transcend mundane political realities like votes and vetoes people 
are drawn to him a guy who tells fellow amputees about the great 
legmaker he found who reads books and drinks beer and goes to 
movies who celebrated his election to the senate by singing a 
long tragic ballad about mutilated young war veterans 
hes a remarkable man said harvard psychiatrist and author 
robert coles who has met with kerrey and corresponds with him 
he hasnt let politics go to his head yet were all praying 
for him 
</TEXT>
