the mississippi glides southward 
it passes grave markers on the battlefield at vicksburg miss 
where grant gained control of the river after a 47day siege it 
flows past mansions at natchez where every spring as in many 
towns confederate uniforms and pastel gowns are put back on and 
the doors open to the public for pilgrimages to the antebellum 
world 
