starring john lithgow and isabella rossellini jones plays a police 
inspector investigating poaching 
i did the narration for the discovery channels ivory wars 
which was about poaching and merchandising illegal ivory he 
said kenya has taken a stand to stop poaching by burning piles 
of confiscated ivory i was in zimbabwe which has a wellmanaged 
elephant control program i brought back some ivory from zimbabwe 
but i had to have a stack of certificates showing that it was not 
poached 
jones is currently working on tnts heat wave a movie about 
the 1965 watts riot in los angeles he plays junius johnson a 
watts community leader who tries to stop the violence that spread 
through seven days of rioting 
