<TEXT>
its about 10 am and the temperature is already 
approaching 90 degrees as abdul akim muhammad drives his aging dark 
blue porsche down the dirt road leading to the home of larry a 
16yearold dropout 
in bygone days theyd have called muhammad a truant officer but 
in these more euphemistic times hes known as the intervention 
specialist at south mountain high school which has gained 
attention for cutting its dropout rate dramatically and quickly 
from 22 percent two years ago to less than 10 percent this spring 
for four years muhammad 49 and a burly 6footer has served on 
the frontlines of the dropout war he prowls local parks and 
convenience stores often spotting absentee kids hanging out 
mainly though he visits as many as 20 homes a day begging 
cajoling and occasionally threatening chronically absent students 
their parents or their grandparents 
muhammed and his porsche are thus familiar sights in the barrios 
and dusty backroads of south phoenix springtime is especially busy 
for muhammad as students look for more interesting diversions than 
school 
pulling up to larrys home barely five miles from the glitter 
and wealth of downtown phoenix muhammad is greeted by larrys 
grandparents an old dog with flies crawling in its eyes huddles in 
the shade 
im from south mountain i wanted to ask you where larry is 
muhammad said larry wasnt home his grandparents said they 
understood hed been suspended from south mountain for good they 
told muhammad their grandson was now working for a high school 
equivalency diploma 
well thats fine ill just check into it muhammad said 
he is an old hand at such excuses truant youngsters often mislead 
parents and grandparents about their daily whereabouts i dont 
take anyones word for it he said 
in this case larrys story checked out 
i really relate to these kinds of people he told a reporter 
accompanying him a lot of these parents dont have an education 
they dont really see the value 
some kids cant stand being successful he said when i 
talk to them sometimes they tell me you dont know what its 
like you dont understand then i say what do you mean i dont 
know and i tell them where i come from 
muhammad grew up in rural orange texas the son of a mill hand 
like many of the parents he now deals with his own folks 
couldnt see the point of staying in school 
he continued in school anyhow and eventually got into counseling 
because he was so good at connecting with youngsters and their 
problems 
nevertheless muhammad thinks schools today including south 
mountain often coddle youngsters 
in some instances we make kids weak he said im guilty 
of it too if they dont like a teacher we promise to find them 
another maybe sometimes i should say too bad youre just going 
to have to work it out 
