smirnoff the onetime vodka of the czars 
banished during the bolshevik revolution is back in the ussr 
with a distinctly american flavor 
heublein inc has taken advantage of easing eastwest trade 
restraints to ship smirnoff back to the soviet union where it was 
first distilled in the 1800s said vivian brooks heubleins 
director of public relations 
smirnoff has really reached the point where it represents all 
that is chic and fashionable about america brooks said 
the farmingtonbased liquor and wine company has been bottling 
vodka under the smirnoff name in the united states for more than 50 
years acquiring the formula from russian exiles in the 1930s 
peter smirnoff first distilled his vodka in 1818 in moscow 
brooks said and through the next century became the official 
supplier of vodka and liqueurs to the court of imperial russia 
in 1917 as the bolsheviks took control of the government 
moscows businesses and industries were taken over by the red army 
and vladimir smirnoff then running the family distillery was 
jailed and sentenced to death as a symbol of czarist oppression 
smirnoff was rescued by the white army and made his way to 
france where in the early 1930s he sold the family formula to 
rudolph ly bought the smirnoff formula 
and rights for heublein in 1939 
