<TEXT>
heres how the electronic data interchange 
system at apparel maker levi strauss amp co works 
levis pretickets its jeans and other items with tags 
containing bar codes similar to those used in supermarkets 
at a retail store electronic scanners at the checkout record 
the information contained on the tags the stores computer records 
the fact that an item has been sold using the information the 
computer can automatically reorder goods from levis 
as orders are shipped by levis the companys distribution 
center generates packing slips and sends them electronically to the 
stores computer the store now knows what is coming and when to 
expect it 
stores receive preticketed levis products in boxes printed 
with a bar code on the side this bar code is crossreferenced to 
the electronic packing slip number when stores scan the bar code 
they eliminate the need to count the merchandise by hand and the 
goods can be sent directly to the store shelves 
under an improvement in the system to be introduced soon 
levis computers will automatically reorder denim and other 
supplies needed to make more jeans to replace those shipped 
