<TEXT>
please no loud noises the corn is taking an 
afternoon nap 
on warm drx afternoons corn takes a photosynthesis siesta 
says the agriculture department and that slows its growth 
plant physiologist james a bunce of the departments 
agricultural research service said the photosynthetic rate dpops a 
total of about 30 percent on warm dry afternoons under normal 
growing conditions 
bunce found the photosynthesis slump in laboratory studies and 
confirmed it in under field conditions the agency reported 
wednesday 
as soon as the humidity directly around the leaves drops the 
leaves dry out slightly and the rate of photosynthesis drops even 
if the soil around the roots of the plant is wet he said 
bunce said it should be possible to find corn varieties that 
react less to humidity decreases or to breed the potential into 
commercial varieties that would allow corn to sleep less and grow 
more 
</TEXT>
