said the loss showed that even a wellrun bank was not immune to 
the severe downturn 
this is fleetnorstar a really good wellmanaged bank 
said gerard cassidy of tucker anthony amp rl day you dont like 
to see these numbers for a good bank it just supports our 
thinking that the new england economy is extremely weak 
an increase in nonperforming assets to 928 million was the 
underlying cause of the loss fleets first since 1974 and most of 
that 552 million was in commercial real estate which has hurt 
other new england banks 
just a month ago fleet had predicted nonperforming assets would 
total a record 600 million but noted that figure could go higher 
based on the results of a joint supervisory review by state and 
federal regulators chief financial officer john w flynn said 
regulators required more assets be included in that category than 
fleet had anticipated 
of the 928 million 412 million of those assets are 
performing assets right now in the sense that they either are 
truly current or less than 90 days past due flynn said 
nonperforming loans of 653 million up 319 million were the 
largest part of the problem real estate on which fleet has 
foreclosed rose 80 million to 275 million 
fleet stressed that although it has some problem areas its 
underlying assets are strong and it expects to return to 
profitability in the second quarter 
analysts were quick to agree with managements assessment 
their veil of invincibility has been pierced said james j 
mcdermott jr of keefe bruyette amp woods but its an exciting 
company with strong capital and should chart its way through 
these difficult times 
as with other regional banks the biggest problem was with 
commercial real estate mostly in the hardpressed new england 
market in fact the companys lead bank outside the region 
albany nybased norstar bank earned a profit of 17 million up 
2 million 
although flynn would not discuss other specific banks he said 
fleet does not anticipate the problems such companies as the 
struggling bank of new england corp have experienced 
numerically our nonperforming assets are lower than others in 
the region he said our equity capital is higher than others 
in the region and over the last two years our earnings have been 
substantially higher obviously we believe we are far more 
diversified than almost anybody in the country 
cassidy agreed noting that fleet is insulated by nonbanking 
income like mortgage banking subsidiaries and student loan 
processing centers which are less influenced by regional economic 
downturns 
long term these guys are going to be survivors and in fact 
theyre going to be expanding and theyre going to be taking 
advantage of the opportunities over the next 12 to 15 months he 
said 
