profits fell by 54 percent at general motors 
corp and by 69 percent at ford motor co in the first quarter due 
to us production slowdowns and problems with overseas operations 
the companies said thursday 
the figures combined with chrysler corps 80 percent drop in 
first quarter net income meant an overall 64 percent profit drop 
for the big three automakers during the period 
but the results were not as bad as the 75 percent profit decline 
that analysts had expected for the companies which are struggling 
with soft markets and intensified competition from foreignbased 
automakers 
the big three earned a combined 129 billion in the quarter 
down from 354 billion in the yearearlier period big three 
revenue during the period fell 11 percent to 6127 billion 
